Add Omni Supervisor to a Lightning App

To add Omni Supervisor to an app in Lightning Experience, ensure that you have:

Omni-Channel enabled and running with agents and queues
A working Lightning app for service

In Setup, navigate to App Manager, edit the app, and:

Add Omni-Channel under Utility Items if it's not already included
Add Omni Supervisor to Navigation Items
Select Use Omni-Channel sidebar (optional)
Assign user profiles that have tab visibility to use Omni Supervisor in their app

Save your work and verify that Omni Channel is in the app by viewing the tab selections. You should see the Omni Supervisor option.

Note: Only status-based capacity models work with standard apps, while tab-based capacity models don't work in such apps.
title: Adding Omni Supervisor to a Lightning App
